# Parameters for pointing this container's `claude` at this repo's own
# llm-gateways Portkey Gateway service instead of api.anthropic.com
# directly. Read by scripts/point-to-gateway.sh (or its "Point Claude CLI
# at a Gateway" menu entry) — see the README's "Pointing Claude CLI at a
# Gateway" section before using this. NOT this environment's own .env —
# kept separate so switching gateways, or reverting, never has to
# hand-edit or lose track of the other gateway's own settings.
#
# host.docker.internal, not a container name or "localhost" — same
# reasoning as .env.gateway.litellm's own comment (separate Compose
# projects, no shared Docker network). Match the port to whatever
# PORTKEY_PORT actually is in environments/llm-gateways/.env (default
# 8787) if you changed it there.
#
# NOT independently verified against a live Portkey Gateway instance from
# inside this repo. Confirm your installed Portkey Gateway version exposes
# an Anthropic-Messages-API-compatible route at this base URL (the shape
# Claude Code's ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL actually needs — see Portkey's own
# docs for the exact path, which may differ from a bare base URL) before
# relying on this: run point-to-gateway.sh, then send `claude` a real
# message and check it actually responds rather than erroring.
ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:8787

# Portkey Gateway ships with no server-side auth of its own (see
# llm-gateways' own README "Security Notes") — it forwards whatever
# credential the caller sends straight through to the upstream provider.
# Set this to whatever key Portkey should forward to Anthropic on your
# behalf, per Portkey's own header-forwarding docs.
ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=
